{
  "texts": [
    "Altogether the researcher observes (r,Y r,W r) for each collected text piece with d r = 1.",
    "To make this more concrete, consider two illustrative empirical applications that we return to throughout the paper.",
    "The economic outcome Y r might be the company's realized return in some event window after the headline's publication date, while the candidate determinant W r of the news headline itself could be the company's past fundamentals.",
    "▲ Importantly, each text piece r expresses some economic concept for which it is costly in terms of either time or money to obtain measurements.",
    "A key assumption in much empirical research (often left implicit) is that there is some existing procedure that could in principle be applied to each text piece to measure the economic concept; that is, the economic concept is defined as the output of some mapping f * (r) for all text pieces r ∈R."
  ]
}